hopobject.body: I never went to university cygnethealth.co.uk But first, she is eager, naturally enough, to trumpet the positives. “When I was starting out,” she recalls of an academic career that began with an Oxford degree in physiology and philosophy, developed into a masters in psychology at Stirling, and then a doctorate in computational neuroscience back in Oxford, “neuroscience was a sub branch of psychology. Now it is a fully-fledged science in its own right. It has,” she pronounces almost regally, “come of age.”
